edge: Yeoh's portrayal of Evelyn in the main universe and Alpha-Evelyn in the Alphaverse are related as they are both versions of the character Evelyn.
Hsu's characters Joy Wang and Jobu Tupaki are related as they are both daughters of Evelyn in different universes, with Jobu becoming increasingly nihilistic.
Quan's characters Waymond Wang and Alpha-Waymond are related as they are both versions of the character Waymond, with Alpha-Waymond coming from the Alphaverse.
Hong's characters Gong Gong and Alpha-Gong Gong are related as they are both versions of the character Gong Gong, with Alpha-Gong Gong coming from the Alphaverse.
Curtis' character Deirdre Beaubeirdre and her alternate universe counterparts are related as they are all variations on the same character.
Shum's character Chad works alongside an alternate version of Evelyn in another universe.
Medel's character Becky Sregor is Joy's girlfriend.
Wiff's character Rick is a laundromat customer.
Mani and Lazar appear as actors in a musical film that Evelyn watches in the main universe.
Wasilewski and Banifaz appear as Alpha RV Officers, who are officers in a research vessel that travels through the multiverse.
Le and Lazar are both actors who appear in the movie 'Everything Everywhere All at Once'.
Aaron Lazar appears as an actor in the musical film that Evelyn watches.
Audrey Wasilewski appears as a member of the Alpha RV Officers.
Peter Banifaz appears as an Alpha Trophy Jumper.
Li Jing appears as Evelyn's kung-fu teacher in the context.
Michiko Nishiwaki appears as Evelyn's kung-fu opponent and co-star in the context.
Randy Newman provides the voice of Raccacoonie from the Pixar animated film Ratatouille in this context.
Scheinert appears as the District Manager in this context.
Kwan appears as a man who is sucked into a bagel in this context, but goes uncredited.
